{"lemma":"صَفَرُ","slug":"صَفَرُ","root":"ص.ف.ر","root_slug":"ص-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَفَرُ","root":"صفر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":11,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun","num","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24452","","n24456","n24457","n24458","n24459","n24460","n24461"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"Safar (the second month of the Islamic calendar)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be empty, to be devoid, to be vacant"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to empty, to void, to vacate, to evacuate, to free"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"empty, void, devoid, free from"},{"pos":"num","gloss":"zero","examples":[{"text":"Next: واحد, or ١ = 1"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dye yellow, to make yellow, to color yellow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"brass"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"money"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَفِرَ (ṣafira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jaundice"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"plural of أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to whistle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hiss"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chirp, to stridulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to scream (of a siren)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to whistle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hiss"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chirp, to stridulate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to scream (of a siren)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From ص ف ر (ṣ f r, “void”), supposedly because pagan Arabs looted during this month and left the houses empty.\n\nSemantic loan from Sanskrit शून्य (śūnya), also with the original meaning of “empty, void”. Compare صَفْر (ṣafr, “empty, void”) (also صِفْر (ṣifr)).\n\nCausative from the root ص ف ر (ṣ f r), from which the color or defect adjective أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”) also comes.\n\nRelated to أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”), from the root ص ف ر (ṣ f r).\n\nIn its meaning \"jaundice\", related to أَصْفَر (ʔaṣfar, “yellow”), from the root ص ف ر (ṣ f r).\n\nInflected form.\n\nPresumably, originally an intensive of صَفَرَ (ṣafara, “to whistle, hiss, chirp”), later losing its intensive sense."},"ipa":["/sˤa.far/","/sˤifr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24452","headword_ar":"صَفَرَ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafiyrN","text_ar":"صَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) with which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufaArN","text_ar":"صُفَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. in a phrase mentioned below; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sf~r","text_ar":"صفّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSofiyrN","text_ar":"تَصْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird, a vulture, S, and a serpent, or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowad","text_ar":"اَسْوَد"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraj","text_ar":"اَعْرَج"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibon qitorap","text_ar":"اِبْن قِتْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSalap","text_ar":"اَصَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whistled;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mkaA","text_ar":"مكَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered, a certain sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, * K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without the utterance of letters."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [It is mostly said of a bird: see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaw~N","text_ar":"جَوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] One says [also],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safara","text_ar":"صَفَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlS~af~aArapi","text_ar":"فِى الصَّفَّارَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He whistled in the whistle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safara biAloHimaAri","text_ar":"صَفَرَ بِالْحِمَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sf~r","text_ar":"صفّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He called the ass to water"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by whistling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for to do thus is the common custom of the Arabs]. (M, K.) And Fr mentions the phrase, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna fiY kalaAmihi SafaArN","text_ar":"كَانَ فِى كَلَامِهِ صَفَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafiyrN","text_ar":"صَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There was in his speech a whistling"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safira","text_ar":"صَفِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafarN","text_ar":"صَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufuwrN","text_ar":"صُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and accord. to the T,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safara","text_ar":"صَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufuwrapN","text_ar":"صُفُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, empty, void,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vacant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K;) namely, a house or tent; (S;) or a vessel, (S, M, &c.,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina AlT~aEaAmi waAl$~araAbi","text_ar":"مِنَ الطَّعَامِ وَالشَّرَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of food and beverage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and a skin,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina All~abani","text_ar":"مِنَ اللَّبَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) and a hand; (A;) and a thing; (S, M;) and accord. to ISk,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safira","text_ar":"صَفِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafiyrN","text_ar":"صَفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is said of a man. (TA.) [See also 4, last sentence but one.] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEuw*u biAll~`hi mino qaraEi AlfinaA='i waSafari","text_ar":"نَعُوذُ بِاللّٰهِ مِنْ قَرَعِ الفِنَا=ءِ وَصَفَرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_inaA='i","text_ar":"الاـِنَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We seek preservation by God from the yard's becoming void of cattle, and the vessel's becoming empty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the perishing of the cattle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safirato wiTaAbuhu","text_ar":"صَفِرَتْ وِطَابُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waToAatuhu","text_ar":"وَطْاَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safira A_inaAw^uhu","text_ar":"صَفِرَ اـِنَاوُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His milk-skins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his vessel, became empty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he died;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he perished."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A. [See also other explanations in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wTb","text_ar":"وطب"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sufira","text_ar":"صُفِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaforN","text_ar":"صَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufaAr","text_ar":"صُفَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow water in his belly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","A"]},{"entry_id":"n24456","headword_ar":"صَفْرٌ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24457","headword_ar":"صُفْرٌ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also, (S, M, A, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to AO, (S, M, Msb, *) who allowed no other form, but the former is the better, (M,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Brass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"metal of which vessels are made;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuHaAsN","text_ar":"نُحَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means both"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copper"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuHaAs","text_ar":"نُحَاس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuHaAs","text_ar":"نُحَاس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made yellow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best sort of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuHaAs","text_ar":"نُحَاس"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excellent sort thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) n. un. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforapN","text_ar":"صُفْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aforaA='u","text_ar":"الصَّفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaru","text_ar":"اَصْفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deenars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"either because they are yellow ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforN","text_ar":"صُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaru","text_ar":"اَصْفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]), or thus called because resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sufor","text_ar":"صُفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which vessels are made. (M.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Women's ornaments."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lafiY Suforihi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَفِى صُفْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA, [thus in an old and very excellent copy of the S, in another copy of which I find, as in Freytag's Lex., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforapK","text_ar":"صُفْرَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Siforihi","text_ar":"صِفْرِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [app. means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is in that state in which he requires to be rubbed with saffron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it] is said of him who is affected by madness, when he is in the days in which his reason fails; because they used to rub him with somewhat of saffron. (S, O, L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n24458","headword_ar":"صِفْرٌ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforN","text_ar":"صُفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufurN","text_ar":"صُفُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafirN","text_ar":"صَفِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaforN","text_ar":"صَفْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaru","text_ar":"اَصْفَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Empty, void,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vacant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K;) applied to a house or tent, (S, Msb,) and to a vessel, (M, A,) and to a hand: (A:) each of the first three is used alike as masc. and fem. and sing. [and dual] and pl.: (M:) [and so, app., is the last but one:] and each has also for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaArN","text_ar":"اَصْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotN SiforN mina AlmataAEi","text_ar":"بَيْتٌ صِفْرٌ مِنَ المَتَاعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber, empty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"void, of furniture and utensils."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And [applying the pl. form of the epithet to a sing. subst.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inaA='N A^aSofaArN","text_ar":"اـِنَا=ءٌ اَصْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An empty vessel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) like as one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buromapN A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"بُرْمَةٌ اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; on the authority of IAar: (M:) and [applying the sing form of the epithet to a pl. subst.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=niyapN SiforN","text_ar":"ا=نِيَةٌ صِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"empty vessels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN Siforu Alyadayoni","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ صِفْرُ اليَدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man empty-handed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN mina Alxayori","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ مِنَ الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Void of good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said, in a trad., of Umm-Zara, that she was"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN ridaAw^uhaA","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ رِدَاوُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lank in her belly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rdA'","text_ar":"رداء"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a garment that falls upon the belly and there ends, were empty. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa SiforN SiHorN","text_ar":"هُوَ صِفْرٌ صِحْرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utterly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"empty;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SHr","text_ar":"صحر"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an imitative sequent. (Kh, Ham p. 354.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in arithmetical notation, in the Indian method, is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A circle"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or the character"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":", denoting"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"zero;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence our term “ cipher: ” when nought is thus denoted, five is denoted by a character resembling our B: but more commonly, in the present day, nought is denoted by a round dot; and five, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L, TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforN","text_ar":"صُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n24459","headword_ar":"صَفَرٌ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safira","text_ar":"صَفِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.: ―         -b2-  and hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hunger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaforapN","text_ar":"صَفْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the inf. n. un.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hungering once."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease in the belly, which renders the face yellow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collecting of water in the belly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kt.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufaArN","text_ar":"صُفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of serpent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the belly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which sticks to the ribs, and bites them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) or, as the Arabs assert,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which bites a man when he is hungry, its bite occasioning the stinging which a man feels when he is hungry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) used alike as sing. and pl.; or one is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafarapN","text_ar":"صَفَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and it is said to be what is meant by the word in a trad., in which it is disacknowledged: (S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain reptile"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~ap","text_ar":"دَابَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which bites the ribs and their cartilages:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain serpent in the belly, which attacks beasts and men, and which, accord. to the Arabs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the time of Ignorance"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passes from one to another more than the mange or scab;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ru-beh:) the Prophet, however, denied its doing so: it is said also that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it oppresses and hurts a man when he is hungry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd:) this is the explanation approved by Az: (TA:) or, as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SufaArN","text_ar":"صُفَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worms in the belly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in the cartilages of the ribs, which cause a man to become very yellow, and sometimes kill him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaD~a EalaY $urosuwfihi AlS~afaru","text_ar":"عَضَّ عَلَى شُرْسُوفِهِ الصَّفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was hungry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)       -A2-  Accord. to some, (M,) in the trad. above referred to,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafarN","text_ar":"صَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"postponing of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the month"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Moharram, transferring it to Safar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, M, K:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiYo'N","text_ar":"نَسِىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or it there means the disease called by this name, because they asserted it to be transitive. (K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1698},{"kind":"text","text":"Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwEN","text_ar":"رُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K: [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoE","text_ar":"رَوْع"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inmost part"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lub~","text_ar":"لُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) Hence the saying, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yalotaATu h`*aA biSafariY","text_ar":"لَا يَلْتَاطُ هٰذَا بِصَفَرِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This will not adhere to me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to my mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor will my soul accept it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) said of that which one does not love. (A.)       -A4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A contract, compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covenant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suretiship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"responsibility:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqodN","text_ar":"عَقْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, L, K. [In some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fqd","text_ar":"فقد"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A5-  Also (S, M, Msb, K) and sometimes ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safaru","text_ar":"صَفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] imperfectly decl., (K,) but all make it perfectly decl. except AO, who makes it imperfectly decl. because it is determinate [or a proper name] and similar in meaning to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEapN","text_ar":"سَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is fem., meaning that all nouns signifying times are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEaAt","text_ar":"سَاعَات"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, M,) and, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~afaru","text_ar":"الصَّفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The second month of the Arabian calendar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the month that is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the next"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after ElMoharram"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHar~amu","text_ar":"المُحَرَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, M, K:) so called because in it they used to procure their provision of corn from the places [in which it was collected, their granaries having then become empty ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sifor","text_ar":"صِفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"); agreeably with the opinion of my learned friend Mons. Fulgence Fresnel, that it was so called from the scarcity of provisions in the season in which it fell when it was first named; for it then fell in winter: see the latter of the two tables in p. 1254; and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiYo'N","text_ar":"نَسِىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or because Mekkeh was then empty, its people having gone forth to travel: or, accord. to Ru-beh, because the Arabs in it made predatory expeditions, and left those whom they met empty: (M:) or because they then made predatory expeditions, and left the houses of the people empty: (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmd","text_ar":"جمد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaArN","text_ar":"اَصْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafaraAtN","text_ar":"صَفَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~afaraAni","text_ar":"الصَّفَرَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two months of El-Moharram and Safar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two months of the year, whereof one was called by the Muslims El-Moharram."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","TA","Msb","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n24460","headword_ar":"صَفِرٌ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24461","headword_ar":"صُفُرٌ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}